text:
Dwight Street, east side, north from Wolcott Street. The gasoline station in the foreground is in a triangle bounded by Wolcott, Dwight and Otsego Streets.

June 9, 1938.

P.L. Sperr

Lorraine Street, east from Dwight Street. Looking across Otsego Street just beyond the gas station is Todd's Field. Beyond it are houses facing on Columbia Street.

June 9, 1938.

P. L. Sperr

6-18 Wolcott Street north side west from Dwight Street. The building at the corner, not fully shown, is 110 Dwight Street.

June 9, 1938.

P.L. Sperr

Wolcott Street (left, foreground) between Otsego Street (right) and Dwight Street (left). At the right foreground is Lorraine Street. In the background is Dwight Street going off at a tangent. The garage beyond the gas station is on the N.W. corner of Dwight and Sullivan Streets. The steeple seen in the background is a part of the Roman Catholic Church of the visitation.

June 9, 1938.

P. L. Sperr
